  "texts": [
    "On the ideological side, Cantoni et al. (2017) analyze a staggered Chinese curricular reform which caused students (as intended) to be more skeptical of free markets.",
    "3 An inuential working paper by Fisman et al. (2009) found that law students exposed to an economics-trained professor behaved less pro-socially in lab experiments 1 and 3 years later.",
    "Bleemer and Mehta (2020) nd using a regression discontinuity that economics majors tend to earn higher wages by working in higher-paying industries.",
    "Paredes et al. (2020) nd using Chilean data that majoring in economics is correlated with sexism expressed in survey measures.",
    "See also Ifcher and Zarghamee (2018)."
  ]
}